## Overview

REST API client interface for HTTP-based communication with instruments and
services. Provides standard HTTP methods (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE) with session
management and configurable timeouts.

## Usage

```python
from {{ interface_name }}_interface import {{ interface_name | pascal_case }}Interface

interface = {{ interface_name | pascal_case }}Interface(base_url="http://192.168.1.100:8080")
interface.connect()

# Read data
status = interface.get("/api/status")

# Send commands
result = interface.post("/api/command", data={"action": "run", "params": {"speed": 100}})

# Update configuration
interface.put("/api/config", data={"mode": "auto"})

# Remove resources
interface.delete("/api/resource/123")

interface.disconnect()
```

