## Dependencies

- `httpx>=0.24` or `requests>=2.28` for the real interface

## Common Pitfalls

- Ensure the base URL does not include a trailing slash (it is stripped automatically)
- Set an appropriate timeout for slow endpoints; the default is 10 seconds
- Handle HTTP error status codes in your application logic
- Consider retry logic for transient network failures
- Be aware of JSON serialization for request/response bodies
